# P4Nexus — Cursor project rules

Last reviewed: 2026-05-07

Canonical agent instructions: **[AGENTS.md](../AGENTS.md)** (P4Nexus MCP rules, monorepo commands, Cursor Cloud notes). **[CLAUDE.md](../CLAUDE.md)** adds Claude Code-specific notes and points back to AGENTS.md for P4Nexus.

## Non-negotiables (always apply)

- NEVER edit a function/class/method without running `p4nexus_impact` first.
- NEVER rename symbols with find-and-replace — use `p4nexus_rename`.
- NEVER commit without running `p4nexus_detect_changes()`.
- NEVER ignore HIGH/CRITICAL risk warnings from impact analysis.
- NEVER run `npx p4nexus analyze` without `--embeddings` if `.p4nexus/meta.json` shows stored embeddings.

Full rules: **[AGENTS.md](../AGENTS.md)** (`p4nexus:start` block, Cursor Cloud section).

**Rule architecture:** Prefer this file plus optional `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` globs (YAML `globs` in frontmatter). Legacy `.cursorrules` is deprecated; content lives here.
